[
  "# Understanding ",
  "Streaming Render",
  "ing\n\nWhen building a ",
  "markdown renderer that handles ",
  "real-time ",
  "streaming input, the ",
  "key challenge is maintaining ",
  "visual smooth",
  "ness while processing ",
  "**partial content** that arrives ",
  "in arbitrary chunks.",
  " Each chunk may split ",
  "mid-word, mid-",
  "sentence, or even mid-syntax.\n\n",
  "## The Parsing ",
  "Pipeline\n\nThe first ",
  "step is buffering incoming ",
  "text until a complete block ",
  "boundary is detected. A block ",
  "boundary occurs when:\n\n- A blank ",
  "line separates two paragraphs\n",
  "- A code fence opens or ",
  "closes\n- A heading marker ",
  "appears at the start of a line\n",
  "- A list item begins ",
  "with a marker\n\nOnce a boundary ",
  "is detected, the frozen ",
  "blocks are parsed and rendered ",
  "as immutable views.\n\n```swift\n",
  "func processChunk(_ chunk: ",
  "String) {\n    buffer",
  ".append(chunk)\n    let events = ",
  "boundary.scan(",
  "buffer)\n    for event in events ",
  "{\n        reducer.apply(",
  "event)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe buffer ",
  "maintains state between chunks, ",
  "tracking whether we are inside ",
  "a code block, list, or other ",
  "multi-line construct.\n\n### Frozen ",
  "vs Tail Blocks\n\nBlocks that ",
  "have been fully received are ",
  "*frozen* -- they will not change. ",
  "The last block in the stream is ",
  "the *tail block*, which continues ",
  "to receive content.\n\n",
  "| Property | Frozen | Tail |\n",
  "|:---------|:-------|:-----|\n",
  "| Mutable | No | Yes |\n",
  "| Cached | Yes | No |\n",
  "| Re-rendered | Never | Every update |\n",
  "| Highlighted | Yes | Deferred |\n\n",
  "The frozen prefix grows ",
  "monotonically as new block ",
  "boundaries are detected. This ",
  "ensures that previously rendered ",
  "content remains stable while ",
  "only the tail block is subject ",
  "to incremental updates.\n\n",
  "## Performance Considerations",
  "\n\nThe rendering pipeline must ",
  "complete each update cycle ",
  "within the frame budget to avoid ",
  "visible stutters. For 60fps ",
  "rendering, this means each ",
  "append-parse-render cycle should ",
  "complete in under 16.67ms."
]
